Wash and dry all produce.

Peel and dice @kiwi{1}(peeled and diced). Dice @roma tomato{1}(diced). Halve, peel,
and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced); finely dice
a few slices until you have 2 TBSP. Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered).
Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and minced). Halve, core, and thinly slice
@long green pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced) crosswise into strips.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}
and stir to coat.

Stir in 3/4 cup water and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover
and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Kiwi Salsa ==

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine kiwi, tomato, diced onion, and a squeeze
of lime juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Lime Crema ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp}, half the lime zest, and a pinch
of garlic to taste. Stir in @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling
consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Vegetables ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green
pepper and sliced onion; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until
tender and lightly browned, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Add remaining garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Transfer veggies
to a #plate{}.

== Teriyaki Pork ==

Heat another drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat.
Add @ground pork{10%oz}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Using a #spatula{}, press
into an even layer. Cook, without stirring, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up meat into pieces and continue cooking until pork is cooked through,
~{1-2%minutes} more.

Return cooked veggies to pan. Stir in @Kikkoman® Less Sodium Teriyaki Marinade & Sauce{8%tbsp},
@sugar{1%tsp}, and @butter{1%tbsp}. Cook until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in remaining lime zest and season with @salt{}.

Divide rice between bowls and top with pork mixture, kiwi salsa, and garlic lime crema.
Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.